events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/erickbelfy/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-05-23T11:10:43Z","updated_at":"2020-05-23T11:10:43Z","body":"This edge case happened because in some scenarios yup doens't have support for cyclic dependencies, meaning that in a scenario where one fields relies on the other field, Yup raises an error hence i am not able to validate the form properly, so that's why i had to use setError. I undersrtand that the validationSchema is the source of truth, i'd love to not use setError at alll, but in a scenario like this, is pratically impossible to not use.\r\n\r\nlook:\r\n```\r\n{   \r\n          qna: yup.object().shape({\r\n            answer: yup.string().when('question', {\r\n              is: value => value !== '',\r\n              then: yup.string().required(),\r\n              otherwise: yup.string().notRequired(),\r\n            }),\r\n            question: yup.string().when('answer', {\r\n              is: value => value !== '',\r\n              then: yup.string().required(),\r\n              otherwise: yup.string().notRequired(),\r\n            }),\r\n          })\r\n}\r\n```\r\nthis schema will raise an error with yup","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/react-hook-form/react-hook-form/issues/comments/633028734/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"erickbelfy","id":1584725,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1ODQ3MjU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1584725?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/erickbelfy","html_url":"https://github.com/erickbelfy","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/erickbelfy/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/erickbelfy/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/erickbelfy/gists{/gist_i